During this term students study diagnosis and diferential diagnosis of periodontal diseases. They fix periodontal status, plan treatment and perform depuration in periodontal patients with hand-, rotating and ultrasonic instruments, prescrible antiseptic ang antibiotic treatment. The clinical work performed by the student has been analyzed with the tutor, the student has received feedback and the work has been included in the student's e-portfolio.Objectives/eesmärkid:  During the autumn term  students perform more complicated root canal treatmenst and direct restorations. 
During spring term students learn to examine periodontal patient; to diagnose periodontal disease; to register periodontal status; to plan treatment and perform depuration in periodontal patients with hand-, rotating and ultrasonic instruments; to prescrible treatment with antiseptics and antibiotics. Oral mucuopus membrane diseases are lectured.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After this course students can examine periodontal patient; diagnose periodontal disease, evaluate riskfactors of periodontal disease, plan cause-related treatment an remove mechanically dental plaque and calculus supra- and subgingivally; treat emergency cases; prescribe antiseptics and antibiotics for periodontal patients.
